Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=10}===============================DIALOGUE============================
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:01:56.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They've come all this way\Nafter braving the Aqua Laguna. - OG}Despite Aqua Laguna, they've made it here.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.55,0:01:58.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's pretty incredible, honestly. - OG}That's quite impressive, honestly.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.31,0:02:01.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They seem to have some good luck. - OG}They're pretty lucky, sure.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.31,0:02:03.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This time we have permission to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:06.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll be easy since we don't\Nhave to go easy on them. - OG}If we don't need to hold back,\Nthis'll be a cinch.{arch/AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.36,0:02:08.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The drawbridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.48,0:02:12.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. The Franky Family is\Ncurrently fighting to bring it down. - OG}Yeah. The Franky Family is\Nworking hard to lower it.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.53,0:02:16.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Once it comes down,\Nwe can go over to the other side. - OG}The moment it lowers,\Nwe're going to the other side.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.66,0:02:19.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... when it's right in front of us... - OG}{Really now... So close,\Nyet so far away. - Z}Really now... So close, yet so far.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:31.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You idiot... - OG}You...{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:36.01,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Honestly, just how heavy\Nis the burden she carries? - OG}{But just how big is the burden \Nshe's lugging around? - Z}{But... just how big [/i1]is[/i0] the burden\Nshe's lugging around? - Evo}Really... just how big {\i1}is{\i0}\Nthat burden she's lugging around?{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.39,0:02:39.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, CP9!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:40.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.43,0:02:44.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You have my permission to kill them,\Nbut take them on here at the Tower of Justice! - OG}You have my permission to kill them,\Nbut do it here, in the tower!{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.77,0:02:48.98,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{The most important things of\Nall are my life and promotion. - OG}My life and my promotion\Ncome first, no matter what!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.61,0:02:56.32,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{If I let them loose, who’ll protect me\Nif something happens?! - OG}{If I let them all go,\Nwho will protect me if something goes wrong? - Evo}If I let them run wild, who will be there\Nto protect {\i1}me{\i0} when something goes wrong?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:00.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stupid pirates! - OG}You imbecilic pirates!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:06.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Recognize that your brave\Nfront doesn't change anything! - OG}{Just know that your brave front\Nwon't change a damn thing! - Z}{You should recognize that your\Nbravery won't change a damn thing! - Evo}You should recognize that acting brave\Nwon't change a damn thing!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:11.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You’re up against the power\Nof CP9’s assassins...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:16.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and the heft of the Gates of Justice,\Nwhich no one can open! - OG}{and the weight of the Gates of Justice,\Nwhich none can open! - Evo}{and the weight of the Gates of Justice,\Nwhich no man can open! - arch}{\q2}and the weight of the immovable Gates of Justice!{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:18.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And more importantly... - OG}{And lest we forget... - AR}And lest we forget, I have the authority...{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.76,0:03:25.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I have the authority to use this golden transponder snail / to exercise a buster call! - OG}{I have the authority to use this golden transponder snail / and exercise a buster call! - arch}to use this golden transponder\Nsnail and exercise a buster call!{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.44,0:03:28.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A buster call!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:30.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:32.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's the same power that\Nwiped out your homeland - OG}{The same power that\Nwiped out your homeland - Evo: removed the colon to link this to the next sentence}The same power...{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.11,0:03:36.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{exactly 20 years ago, Nico Robin. - OG}{Exactly 20 years ago, Nico Robin. - Z}{exactly twenty years ago, Nico Robin. - Evo: reverted back to original}that wiped out your homeland\Nexactly twenty years ago, Nico Robin.{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:42.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I remember that the following year,\Nthe name "Ohara" had been wiped off of the map. - OG}As I recall, the name "Ohara" had\Ndisappeared from the maps the following year!{arch: I don't think this is the idiomatic "wiped off the map", but literally "on the following year's maps, the name Ohara had vanished [because the island was completely destroyed]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.37,0:03:45.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin's homeland?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:47.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That damn masked jerk! - OG}That masked bastard!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:52.71,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\c&H000000&\3c&H000000&\t(0,733,1,\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H525252&)\t(3903,0,1,\alpha&HFF&)}I have nowhere to go\Nand no home to return to.{Alabasta 21 - 12:54}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.63,0:03:54.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:56.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Not that! - OG}Anything but that!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.72,0:04:00.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a nice reaction. It gives me a thrill. - OG}{That reaction is just the thrill I needed! - Z}What a reaction. I'm thrilled already!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:02.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:07.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Does that mean you want me to press this button to call in a Buster Call?\NHm So? Does it? - OG}{Does that mean you want me to press this button to call in a buster call?\NHm? Does it? - Evo}{\q2}Does that mean you {\i1}want{\i0} me to press this button\Nto summon a buster call? Hm? How about it?{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.44,0:04:13.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Do you really understand what'll\Nhappen when you press it? - OG}{You... You do understand what happens \Nwhen you press it, don't you?! - Z}{You... Do you even understand\Nwhat happens when you press that? - Evo}You... Do you really understand\Nwhat happens when you press that button?{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I do. - OG}Oh, I do.{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:20.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll eliminate the possibility\Nof the pirates escaping from this island! - OG}{It'll eliminate the possibility\Nof any escape from this island! - Z}It'll eliminate any possibility\Nof the pirates leaving this island alive!{arch: I do think "the pirates" has to be in there, even if it's clunkier. He's making clear that he's only thinking about achieving his goal, without any regard for any other consequences.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.24,0:04:23.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Just with this single button. - OG}With just the push of a button.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:25.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's that simple. - OG}It's very simple, really.{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:27.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It won't be that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.62,0:04:31.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Are you remembering something? - OG}Does this bring back some memories?{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:34.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you like, shall I try pressing it? - OG}I can try pressing it, if you'd like.{rangicus}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.21,0:04:37.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Right here, right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:43.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.93,0:04:48.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You sure have a cocky mouth on you! - OG}You still have the nerve\Nto talk back to me, huh?{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.12,0:05:10.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You said that Ohara had\Nbeen wiped off the map. - OG}{Like you said, Ohara had\Nbeen wiped off the map. - Evo}Like you said,\NOhara disappeared from the maps.{arch: Mirroring 03:37}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.04,0:05:13.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Can you see humans on a map?! - OG}But can you see human lives on a map?!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.13,0:05:16.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's because you guys see the world that way... - OG}{This narrow way you people view the world... - arch}The narrow way you people view the world...{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:20.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{that you can do such a cruel thing! - OG}is exactly what allows for such a cruel act!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:34.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The buster call is a merciless power \Nthat disregards all goals! - OG}The buster call is a merciless power\Nthat disregards anything and everyone!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.61,0:05:37.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You mustn't use it. Not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:39.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Never...! - OG}Please!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:40.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.58,0:05:54.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin's over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:54.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Get her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:58.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:00.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All right! - OG}Bull's-eye!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.88,0:06:02.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.97,0:06:03.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're creepy!{Bridges this line with the one at 06:17 and 07:00}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:03.97,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.26,0:06:10.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Monster! Monster! Monster! Monster!\N– Monster! Monster! Monster! Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.44,0:06:17.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The monster hit me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.23,0:06:19.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,She's creepy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:21.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We'll get you for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:46.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.89,0:06:54.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My children came home crying,\Nsaying that you hit them for no reason. - OG}My children came home crying,\Nsaying you hit them for no reason.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:57.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stay away from my children. - OG}Stay away from my kids.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.40,0:07:00.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why don't you say something?! - OG}Well, say something, will you?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.40,0:07:02.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... - OG}What a pain...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.07,0:07:04.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You really are a creepy child. - OG}You really are a creepy child.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:07.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:09.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm not done with you yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.17,0:07:21.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mommy, Mommy, what're we\Nhaving for dinner tonight? - OG}Mommy, what are we\Nhaving for dinner tonight?{08:35}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:22.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What'd you like to eat? - OG}What would you like?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:24.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Um... Um... - OG}What about...? Um...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Rice omelet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.05,0:07:29.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You sure like rice omelets, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:29.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:32.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We have to buy lots of eggs, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.52,0:07:33.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.32,0:07:44.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.24,0:07:46.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry I'm late. - OG}Sorry I'm late.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.45,0:07:48.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aunt Roji?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.67,0:08:01.92,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{"To Robin. Today is..." - OG}"Robin, today is..."{rangicus}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.92,0:08:03.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...our daughter's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:08.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we decided that the three of us\Nwould go out for dinner as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.39,0:08:13.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{There's some bread,\Nso just have that for dinner. - OG}We left bread, so eat some for your dinner.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.89,0:08:16.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't use too much jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:23.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{After dinner, before we get home,\Ndo the dishes, clean the house, - OG}{After dinner, and before we get home,\Ndo the dishes, clean the house, - Z}After dinner, but before we get home:\Ndo the dishes, clean the house,{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.15,0:08:28.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}take the laundry in,\Nand then go upstairs early.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.87,0:08:38.87,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Mommy, what are we\Nhaving for dinner tonight?{07:18}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:40.37,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:43.04,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,609,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}What about...? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:44.63,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Rice omelet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.46,0:08:47.38,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You sure like rice omelets, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.38,0:08:48.09,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:50.47,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,We have to buy lots of eggs, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.47,0:08:52.89,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.78,0:09:13.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oh! There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.66,0:09:14.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin's here! - OG}Robin's almost here!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.95,0:09:16.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Looks like she came to return a book. - OG}{Likely returning a book. - Z}Probably returning a book.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:18.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Everyone, to your positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.38,0:09:27.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Professor Clover!\NI came to return the book I borrowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.84,0:09:33.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,One, two...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:37.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}– Congratulations, Robin!\N– Congratulations, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:36.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.77,0:09:38.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're amazing, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.93,0:09:40.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Just as we'd expect from a genius! - OG}That's a genius for you!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:43.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've got a cake for you! - OG}We got you a cake!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:46.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin, the exam for the doctoral\Ndegree you took the other day... - OG}{Robin, regarding the doctoral exam you took the other day, - Z}{Robin, on the doctoral exam you took recently, - rangicus}Robin, the results are in for your doctoral exam!{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.36,0:09:48.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You quite amazingly got 100% on it! - OG}{well, you achieved a perfect score! - Z}You achieved a perfect score!{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:51.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hence, from today on,\Nwe acknowledge you as an archaeologist. - OG}Henceforth, we acknowledge\Nyou as an archaeologist!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.53,0:09:57.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now you're one of us and\Nwe'll do research together. - OG}Now that you're one of us,\Nwe will conduct research together.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:01.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Here, this proves that you're a scholar. - OG}Here, this certifies that you're a scholar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.00,0:10:02.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Take this, Robin. - OG}Please accept it, Robin.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.50,0:10:05.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm happy for you, Robin. - OG}I'm so proud of you, Robin.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:06.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:13.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{Listen, Robin. You must understand well\Nwhat it means to be an archaeologist. - OG}{Listen, Robin. You must fully understand\Nwhat it means to be an archaeologist. - Evo}Listen, Robin. You must develop a firm grasp of what it means to be an archaeologist.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:15.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes, Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.39,0:10:20.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Knowledge comes from the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:24.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This Tree of Knowledge is 5,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:30.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{For centuries, people have brought massive amounts of books to this tree from the world over. - OG}{\q2}For centuries, people have brought countless books\Nto this tree from all over the world.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:35.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's an irreplaceable treasure\Nfor all of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:39.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This is the world's largest, oldest library\Nand a glorious store of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.04,0:10:45.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Renowned archaeologists from across the seas\Ncome forward and gather under this Tree of Knowledge. - OG}{\q2}Renowned archaeologists from across the seas\Ngather beneath this Tree of Knowledge.{Evo/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.75,0:10:52.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There are no historical mysteries we cannot unlock using these books. - OG}Indeed, thanks to these books,\Nwe can unlock all the mysteries of the past!{Evo/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.30,0:10:54.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Got that, Robin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:10:55.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.84,0:10:59.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'd like to see you contribute to the world - OG}{I'd like to see you contribute to human knowledge - Evo}I'd like to see you researching\Ncultures around the world,{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:03.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{by researching various cultures around the world. - OG}contributing to human knowledge.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:07.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Professor! I'd like to solve the mystery of the gap in history! - OG}Professor! I'd like to solve the mystery\Nbehind the gap in history!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:08.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.65,0:11:09.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No! You shouldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I forbid you to do it, just as I always have. - OG}{That one thing\Nis forbidden, and it always will be! - Z}That is forbidden, and it always will be!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.57,0:11:14.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.53,0:11:19.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If we research the poneglyphs, we'll know\Nwhat happened during the Void Century, right?{Zenef: Just like "(the) Middle Ages" an era like this should get capitalized}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:23.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Why do you know that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:27.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Did you peek into the basement\Nusing your powers?! - OG}Did you peek into the basement\Nusing your abilities?!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:27.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.92,0:11:32.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You should know that trying to decipher\Nthe poneglyphs is a criminal act!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.84,0:11:33.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.97,0:11:36.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.68,0:11:38.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{you guys have been\Nresearching the poneglyphs... - OG}in the basement, late into the night,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.97,0:11:41.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{in the basement late at night! - OG}everyone here researches the poneglyphs!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.68,0:11:44.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin! How come you know that?! - OG}Robin! How do you know that?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:46.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Explain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:49.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Are you saying\Nthat you've been spying on that, too? - OG}{Evo: @ Gaijin, as I mentioned on Discord could you check if there is an alternative translation for one or more of the lines that better conveys this scene? They mention the basement twice and Clover looks more clueless than he should be by asking about the same thing again.}Are you saying you saw that, too?{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:52.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Answer me, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.44,0:11:54.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.90,0:11:59.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{if I just walked up,\Nyou wouldn't let me in! - OG}if I'd just walked up,\Nyou wouldn't have let me in!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.87,0:12:02.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.41,0:12:07.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{you'd let me be part of your\Nresearch if I became an archaeologist. - OG}{you'd let me be a part of your\Nresearch if I became an archaeologist. - Evo}{you'd let me join in on your\Nresearch if I became an archaeologist. -Z}you'd let me join in your research\Nif I became an archaeologist.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.58,0:12:10.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So I studied very hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:13.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:22.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's true that you've acquired\Nenough knowledge to be called a scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.55,0:12:25.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But you're still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.64,0:12:29.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If they find out what we're doing,\Nour heads will roll. - OG}If word ever got out about our research,\Nour heads would roll.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.27,0:12:32.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We're{\i0} doing it fully aware of the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:36.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ever since it became law 800 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.40,0:12:41.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{there actually have been numerous\Nscholars who lost their lives. - OG}{numerous scholars have actually\Nlost their lives because of it. - Z}many scholars have lost their lives\Nin pursuit of forbidden knowledge.{Evo: he's talking to a child so watering it down a bit}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.49,0:12:44.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is a good opportunity,\Nso let me tell you this. - OG}Now is as good as ever for you to hear this.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.66,0:12:48.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The Ohara researchers\Nare the only ones in history
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:51.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,who've managed to decipher the ancient texts.{Evo: is he really saying that they're the only ones who managed it at all? Or is it more like "who've gotten this far in deciphering the ancient texts"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:54.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We cannot go back. - OG}We cannot turn back.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.30,0:12:59.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Swear to the Tree of Knowledge: If you try to approach the basement again, - OG}Swear to the Tree of Knowledge:\NYou will never go near the basement again!{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:04.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll forbid you from entering the research lab\Nand the library! - OG}If you do, you will be barred entry\Nfrom both the lab and the library!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:05.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Got that? - OG}Understood?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.52,0:13:10.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.40,0:13:15.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,She's following in her mother's\Nfootsteps in every way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.19,0:13:18.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,She still doesn't know\Nabout the incident from the other day.{Evo: moved up the line break by one word.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:23.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin's mother, Olvia, has been captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.20,0:13:27.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\t(2022,0,1,\c&H000000&)}Her fate is already sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:19.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,W... W...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.76,0:14:23.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Worms?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.23,0:14:34.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That hit the spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:45.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I’m alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.66,0:14:48.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she's okay, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:53.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm safe for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.21,0:14:54.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.46,0:14:57.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is there a town or something on this island?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:14:58.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:00.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:06.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If I was going to drift to somewhere,\NI would've liked an uninhabited island. - OG}If I was going to wash up somewhere,\Nan uninhabited island would've been better.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:17.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You can stay there if you want,\Nbut nothing's gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.40,0:15:23.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My leg got injured, so I'll stay put here. - OG}{My leg was injured, so I gotta stay put. - Z}I busted up my leg, so I've gotta stay put.{Z/Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:29.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm planning to make a raft or\Nsomething and leave here eventually. - OG}{I plan on eventually making a raft\Nand getting outta here. - Z}I plan on eventually making a raft\Nand getting outta here.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:32.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This your first time seeing a giant?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.87,0:15:34.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yep. - OG}Uh-huh.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:40.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm telling you, don't lump me in with those guys from Elbaph. - OG}Then do me a favor and don't lump me in\Nwith those guys from Elbaph.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:44.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There are peaceful giant folk too.
Comment: 0,0:15:44.17,0:15:46.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see... - OG}Hmm...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:50.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I know it's a long shot, but I'll ask you anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:55.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When you get home,\NI don't want you to tell anyone about me. - OG}When you get home, I'd appreciate it\Nif you kept quiet about me.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:57.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.60,0:16:00.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That was too easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.36,0:16:02.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,She'll definitely tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:04.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I won't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:09.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a lie! - OG}I'd like to believe you!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:13.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There's no way\Nthat a child can keep a secret. - OG}There's just no way a child can keep a secret.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:17.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I won't tell because\NI'm not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:34.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,"Dereshi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.77,0:16:36.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.77,0:16:39.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What does it mean? I'm just laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.40,0:16:43.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're laughing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.27,0:16:46.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're a funny girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.49,0:16:52.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a weird way of laughing. - OG}What a weird laugh!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:17:00.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I've always been told that\NI'm not good at laughing. - OG}{I've always been told that\NI'm no good at laughing. - Z}People have always told me\NI'm no good at laughing.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.83,0:17:03.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're cute when you laugh. - OG}{\i1}You've{\i0} got a cute laugh, though.{Evo/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.84,0:17:04.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:06.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You should laugh more!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.26,0:17:11.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,My name is Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:14.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Jaguar D. Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.14,0:17:16.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,"D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.22,0:17:17.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:23.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, but everyone\Nin my family has it in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.44,0:17:24.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:26.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.19,0:17:31.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, Robin,\Npeople are after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:34.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So if people find me, I'll be in trouble. - OG}I'll be in big trouble if I'm spotted.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.24,0:17:36.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\t(397,0,1,\c&H000000&)}{I said I wouldn't tell! - OG}I said I won't tell!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:48.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That was delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:50.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Here's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.59,0:17:56.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I appreciate the thought,\Nbut you go ahead and eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:59.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I’m not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:02.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I caught and ate some fish last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:05.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.56,0:18:08.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, it'll be completed soon.- OG}Well, I'll keep working on my raft.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.78,0:18:11.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll keep working on building a raft. - OG}{I'll keep working on my raft. - Z}It'll be completed soon.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.28,0:18:20.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, you sure have lots\Nof time on your hands, huh? - OG}{Come to think of it, you sure have\Na lot of time on your hands, huh? - Z}In any case, you've sure got\Nlots of time on your hands, huh?{Z/Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.08,0:18:24.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You've been with me all day long\Nfor the past several days. - OG}You've been with me nonstop\Nfor the past several days.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.08,0:18:26.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Your friends and parents will get suspicious. - OG}{You'll worry your friends and family. - Z}You'll worry your parents and friends.{AR- Dialogue flows awkward if parents are not explictly mentioned here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.59,0:18:29.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I don't have parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.51,0:18:34.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, I do have a mother, but she set sail for work when I was small and hasn't come back. - OG}{I mean, I do have a mother, but she's been working away from the island since I was little. - Z}Well, I do have a mother, but she's been\Nworking far away since I was little.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.80,0:18:36.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So, I don't even remember her face. - OG}I don't even remember her face.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:43.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I like those archaeologists, but they don't include me in their research, so I feel left out. - OG}{\q2}I like the archaeologists here, but they keep me\Naway from their research, so I feel left out.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:48.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Kids in town say that I'm creepy,\Nso I won't play with them. - OG}Kids in town say that I'm creepy,\Nso I don't want to play with them.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.86,0:18:54.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, so you're a devil fruit user, huh? - OG}Oh, so you've eaten a devil fruit, huh?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.11,0:18:56.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You aren't scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:19:02.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I've traveled the Grand Line, so I've seen tons of powerful devil fruit users. - OG}I've traveled the Grand Line,\Nso I've seen tons of powerful devil fruits.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:05.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.37,0:19:06.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:08.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That looks convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:18.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You really do laugh in a weird way. - OG}Your laugh really is weird.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:22.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Weird or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.31,0:19:23.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:27.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,if you laugh, it'll make you happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.81,0:19:28.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.86,0:19:32.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,"Why?" When you're having fun, you laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:37.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So if you laugh, you'll have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:41.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Although you're only a child,\Nyou seem to be having a hard time. - OG}Although you're only a child,\Nyou seem to be going through hard times.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.74,0:19:43.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So laugh.{Enies 10 - 10:37}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:45.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When you're having\Na hard time, just laugh! - OG}When the pain gets\Nto be too much, just laugh.{Enies 10 - 10:39}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:48.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It seems stupid to laugh\Nwhen you're having a hard time. - OG}It seems dumb to laugh\Nwhen you're in pain.{Z}{Enies 10 - 10:42}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.38,0:19:50.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's not true.{Enies 10 - 10:44}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:52.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go ahead, give it a shot! - OG}Go ahead!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:55.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go ahead, give it a shot! - OG}Give it your best shot!{Z}
Comment: 0,0:20:00.68,0:20:02.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Deresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:04.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.39,0:20:06.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Do it like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:16.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's good! That's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.70,0:20:23.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is Marine Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.45,0:20:25.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chief Spandine, please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.08,0:20:27.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They want to talk to you, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.96,0:20:31.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Just ignore it. I'm sure they\Njust want a status report. - OG}Ignore it. I'm sure they\Njust want a status report.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.63,0:20:34.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}We'll contact them when we see the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.38,0:20:37.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I don't care whether it's Ohara or Opera,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.88,0:20:41.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}why do I have to come\Nall the way to the West Blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.35,0:20:44.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.10,0:20:46.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What a worthless mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.41,0:21:09.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, is it true that a Marine ship came here? - OG}Hey, is it true that a Marine ship is here?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:10.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What? A Marine ship did? - OG}What? A Marine ship?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.92,0:21:13.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, I heard that it was\Nanchored here when day broke. - OG}Yeah, I heard it was found\Nanchored here at dawn.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.63,0:21:15.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Why would the Marines come...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.55,0:21:17.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,...to such a remote island?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.26,0:21:21.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But no one has seen any Marines on it. - OG}But there are no Marines in sight.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:22.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:25.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No one's on it. It's like a ghost ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:27.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:29.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:31.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:35.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.57,0:21:41.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't believe it, but a Marine ship\Nis anchored at the shore! - OG}I don't believe it, but a Marine ship\Nis anchored at the shore!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.24,0:21:44.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's likely an investigation.\NWe should be cautious, just in case! - OG}It's likely an investigation.\NWe should be extra cautious!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.03,0:21:47.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let the scholars know. - OG}Inform all the scholars.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:53.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The raft's done! - OG}{I just finished the raft! - Z}And the raft's done!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.05,0:22:01.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Then... you're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.09,0:22:02.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.97,0:22:06.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You've got "I'm lonely"\Nwritten all over your face. - OG}You've got "I'll be lonely"\Nwritten all over your face.{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:11.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Come to think of it, I was thinking\Nof attaching a flag or something. - OG}Come to think of it, I was considering\Nputting a flag or something on it.{rangicus/AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.23,0:22:13.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So I'll stay here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.94,0:22:22.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,To sea...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.40,0:22:25.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So you wanna set out to sea, too? - OG}So you wanna leave the island too?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.03,0:22:25.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.78,0:22:30.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,My mother has been busy with her\Narchaeological research all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.71,0:22:34.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But when she comes back\Nto this island next time, - OG}But the next time she\Ncomes back to the island,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.54,0:22:37.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask her\Nto take me with her to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:42.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So I studied hard and I was finally\Nable to become an archaeologist. - OG}{It's why I studied so hard and was finally\Nable to become an archaeologist. - Z}That's why I studied so hard and was finally\Nable to become an archaeologist.{rangicus}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.13,0:22:44.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,An archaeologist?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.01,0:22:45.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When you're still so small? - OG}When you're still a young'un?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.43,0:22:47.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.93,0:22:49.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.26,0:22:53.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,you don't even remember\Nyour mother's face, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.81,0:22:56.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Right... but she's still my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.36,0:22:58.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I wanna see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:03.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Say, Saul...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.57,0:23:08.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Did you know that history has a big gap\Nof 100 years that no one knows about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.20,0:23:12.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's called the Void Century.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.41,0:23:16.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm curious about it, but the government\Nprohibits people from investigating, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:22.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I heard that my mother is\Ntraveling around the world investigating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:26.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But don't tell anyone about it,\Nsince it's actually a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.43,0:23:27.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:33.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{C-Could you mean that she's traveling\Nin search of those stones called poneglyphs? - OG}C-Could that mean that she's traveling\Nin search of those stones called poneglyphs?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.10,0:23:35.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So you know about the poneglyphs? - OG}You know about the poneglyphs?{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:37.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:41.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But don't talk\Nabout it in front of people, okay?! - OG}But don't mention them\Nin front of other people, okay?!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.15,0:23:45.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, about your\Nmother traveling in search of–
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.49,0:23:49.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.99,0:23:54.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin... do you know your mother's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.58,0:23:55.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.54,0:23:59.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's Nico Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.68,0:24:07.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Saul?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.26,0:24:11.85,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin is... Olvia's daughter! - OG}Robin... is Olvia's daughter!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.18,0:24:14.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Then... could this place be...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:17.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,an island called Ohara?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:18.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.56,0:24:21.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This is terrible! Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:26.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So I drifted to Ohara?! - OG}{Then, I drifted to Ohara?! - Z}I actually drifted to Ohara?!{Evo: normally I would like "then" better here, but not when it repeats after line 308}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.61,0:24:28.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is no time to be sitting around talking! - OG}There's no time to chat!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.99,0:24:29.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.70,0:24:30.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.41,0:24:34.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This might shock you,\Nbut listen to me carefully! - OG}This might come as a shock,\Nbut I need you to listen carefully!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.45,0:24:38.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Marine battleships should be\Nheaded to Ohara {\i1}right now{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.29,0:24:41.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The Marines? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.21,0:24:44.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,In order to eliminate\Nthe scholars on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.71,0:24:47.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eliminate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.47,0:24:51.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't tell the...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.34,0:24:54.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't tell the government you're a scholar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.10,0:24:55.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Got that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.51,0:24:51.72,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,That's a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.64,0:24:54.93,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,That's a lie...!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.31,0:24:57.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.68,0:24:59.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.06,0:25:01.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'd never lie to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.15,0:25:04.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go to town now and see if anything\Nstrange has been happening! - OG}Go to town right now to see\Nif anything strange is happening!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.32,0:25:07.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's possible your mother might be back, too! - OG}It's possible your mother came back, too!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.69,0:25:08.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.83,0:25:19.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's been a while, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.04,0:25:20.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.04,0:25:21.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia...!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.04,0:25:23.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So it was you who came on that Marine ship! - OG}So you were the one on that Marine ship!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.42,0:25:25.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We thought you had been caught by the Marines... -OG}We thought they'd captured you!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.84,0:25:36.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry that I came back bearing bad news. - OG}I'm sorry that bad news\Naccompanied my return.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.22,0:25:37.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But what I just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.93,0:25:42.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So the government has finally\Nset its sights on Ohara? - OG}Meaning the government has finally\Nset its sights on Ohara?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.81,0:25:44.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Did you read the newspaper? - OG}Did you hear the news?{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.56,0:25:49.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The poneglyph search team that set off\Nfrom Ohara six years ago was annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.44,0:25:51.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All of them except for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.20,0:25:54.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A total of thirty-three members...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.32,0:25:56.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I was also temporarily captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.83,0:26:01.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The government carefully analyzed\Nmy murdered companions’ belongings
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.50,0:26:04.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,and discovered that we came from Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.71,0:26:07.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is inexcusable! - OG}I have no excuse!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.38,0:26:10.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that this\Nisland is now in danger because of us! - OG}Everyone on this island is in danger\Nbecause of our actions!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.67,0:26:14.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop it! It's no one's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.39,0:26:18.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Those who set out to sea and those\Nwho stayed here—we're all one team!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:21.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You were the ones having a hard time. - OG}You were the ones truly suffering.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.94,0:26:24.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We put you through a terrible ordeal. - OG}You've been through hell.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.23,0:26:27.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.98,0:26:31.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Talented scholars from around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.95,0:26:34.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,gather in Ohara to pursue history,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.86,0:26:37.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,and the government has\Nalways considered us a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.24,0:26:41.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They must think they finally\Nhave something on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.33,0:26:43.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're not gonna pass up this opportunity. - OG}They won't pass up such an opportunity.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.67,0:26:48.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes, but we found out before it was too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.00,0:26:52.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, they will eliminate\Nall known scholars in Ohara!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.72,0:26:56.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Everyone, we must\Nescape Ohara immediately! - OG}{And now, everyone, we must\Nescape Ohara immediately! - Z}So, everyone, we must\Nescape Ohara immediately!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.09,0:26:58.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah... - OG}You're right.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.10,0:27:03.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{this time, we probably won't be\Nable to slip past their investigation like we usually do... - OG}{Unfortunately, it doesn't seem likely that we\Ncan slip past their investigation like usual... - Evo}Unfortunately, I don't think we'll be able\Nto slip past their investigation like usual...{Z - syntax was better, but we ended up with the redundant "likely" and "like"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.43,0:27:07.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{if they are trying to kill us. - OG}especially if they plan to kill us.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.15,0:27:08.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Then, hurry up and–
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.86,0:27:10.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But you know, Olvia,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.03,0:27:15.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't run away leaving this\Ntreasure of mankind behind. - OG}{I can't just run and leave behind\Nthe treasures of humanity. - Z}I can't just run and leave behind\Nthis treasure of humanity.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.28,0:27:16.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.78,0:27:19.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We feel the same way, Olvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.16,0:27:21.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.58,0:27:24.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We don't know what the government is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.33,0:27:28.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But if we run, the precious history\Nthat exists here won't be protected. - OG}But escaping means our precious history\Nwill no longer be protected.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.42,0:27:30.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We'll try whatever we can,\Njust like we always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.92,0:27:32.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.17,0:27:35.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{there must be something\Nweighing on your mind. - OG}there's surely one more thing\Nweighing on you.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.76,0:27:39.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But I can't see her. - OG}But... I can't see her.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.97,0:27:41.72,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Make up your mind, Olvia!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:43.98,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna come aboard the ship or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.98,0:27:46.56,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Stay if you're gonna regret leaving your child!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.56,0:27:48.69,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{If it's about heartache for your husband, we will… - OG}We'll fulfill your husband's dream, so–{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.56,0:27:51.19,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,No! I'll come with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.19,0:27:53.57,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm a scholar of Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.57,0:27:56.86,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I can't abandon the will of our forebears!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.82,0:27:59.24,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.24,0:28:02.99,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll be home after we solve all the mysteries! - OG}{I'll be home once we solve every mystery! - Z}I'll be home once we've solved every mystery!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.25,0:28:10.92,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.92,0:28:13.59,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Where's Mommy? Where did Mommy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.59,0:28:16.09,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Your mother set out to sea for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.09,0:28:18.76,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You'll stay here with us for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.76,0:28:21.72,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You're noisy! Be quiet or I'll hit you!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.72,0:28:23.81,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop it. She's only two.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.81,0:28:25.73,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Our daughter is two, too. - OG}Our daughter is also two.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.73,0:28:28.27,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't care whether she's your\Nbig sister's child or whatever– - OG}{So she's your big sister's kid, huh? - Z}I don't care that she's your sister's child.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.27,0:28:31.40,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{how dare you take in such a burden?! - OG}How dare you impose\Nsuch a burden on us!{Z}
Comment: 0,0:28:32.86,0:28:34.65,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.65,0:28:35.82,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.82,0:28:37.57,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.36,0:28:42.28,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,U-Um... I... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.66,0:28:46.91,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.08,0:28:52.54,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,When you wanna read books,\Njust let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.54,0:28:55.51,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{But I don't have money, so... - OG}But I don't have any money...{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.88,0:28:57.63,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You don't have to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.63,0:29:00.13,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You can read them all for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.13,0:29:00.76,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Free?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.76,0:29:04.26,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, since this is\Nthe best library in the world. - OG}Yeah, since this is\Nthe greatest library in the world.{Z}{Enies 10 - 10:17 (kinda)}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.26,0:29:05.39,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{The best one in the world? - OG}The greatest?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.39,0:29:06.64,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.64,0:29:09.48,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{By the way, you're Olvia's daughter, right? - OG}By the way, you're\NOlvia's daughter, aren't you?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.48,0:29:11.94,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Do you like books?{Enies 10 - 10:20}
Comment: 0,0:29:12.31,0:29:13.36,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.94,0:29:18.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,She looks just like you did\Nwhen you were a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:20.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And like you were at that age,\Nshe's a rare genius, too. - OG}And just like you at that age,\Nshe's a prodigy.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.03,0:29:24.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So long as I know she's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.74,0:29:29.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm too far down this path,\Nso I must sever ties.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.58,0:29:32.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't make her the daughter of a criminal. - OG}{I won't stand for her to become\Nthe daughter of a criminal. - Z}I can't let her become known\Nas a criminal's daughter.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.96,0:29:36.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Professor Clover! This time, a ship flying\Nthe World Government's flag has come! - OG}Professor Clover! This time, there's a ship\Nflying a World Government flag!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.17,0:29:41.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A government ship has come\Nall the way to the West Blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.05,0:29:44.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It indeed seems quite serious. - OG}{Indeed this seems quite serious. - Z}This seems quite serious, indeed.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.93,0:29:48.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Everyone, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.43,0:29:51.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You guys and I are neither fellow scholars\Nnor acquaintances. - OG}We are neither fellow scholars\Nnor acquaintances.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.02,0:29:57.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Keep that in mind, no matter what happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.23,0:30:00.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wait, Olvia! What are you going to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.15,0:30:03.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{Hey, let the headquarters know\Nthat we arrived at our destination. - OG}Hey, notify headquarters\Nthat we've reached our destination.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.99,0:30:07.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, go, go, go! Keep on moving! - OG}Now, go, go, go! Keep it moving!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.66,0:30:10.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... What a pain. - OG}My goodness... What a pain.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.33,0:30:14.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,In any case, this work had\Nbetter get me a promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.46,0:30:18.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, go get all the scholars\Nand restrain them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.46,0:30:19.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Yes, sir!\N– Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.80,0:30:20.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.92,0:30:23.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A woman with a gun is running around!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.86,0:30:43.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{For heaven's sake! - OG}How terrible!{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.74,0:30:46.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.70,0:30:47.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Vice Admiral Kuzan!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.87,0:30:49.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Huh...? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.95,0:30:53.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{We've been notified that CP9's Chief Spandine has arrived in Ohara. - OG}{We've been notified that CP9's Chief Spandine arrived in Ohara! - Evo}It seems Chief Spandine of CP9\Nhas arrived in Ohara.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.66,0:30:55.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.79,0:30:57.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Is that something so important
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.54,0:30:59.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}that you had to wake me up to tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.55,0:31:01.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I-I'm sorry!
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=11}===============================DIALOGUE============================
